io.jeo.filter

Interface FilterVisitor<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanFilterAdapter, FilterAdapter, FilterSplitter, FilterSQLEncoder, FilterWalker, GeoPkgFilterSQLEncoder, PostGISFilterEncoder, StrictFilterAdapter

    public interface FilterVisitor<T>
    Visitor for filter classes.

    Each visit method takes an instance of either Expression or Filter, as well as a an additional object as a "hint" or "context". This object is usually used by the filter visitor itself to pass state around. It is often null.

    Author:
    Justin Deoliveira, Boundless
